<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Summary:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Using <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>GV:Earth</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> primarily to root the enemy, rather than tank or deal damage, using <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Damage Over Time</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> spells or perhaps lower damage nukes to deal the damage.  Likely improved by <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Improved Reclaim Energy, Quick Summoning, Elemental Pact, Pet Discipline</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, etc.  Advantage is that rooted enemy is taking but not dealing damage.<br>
<br>
For lack of a better name, I dub this technique <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Roto-Rooting</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  If it can be successfully mastered and broadly applied, this tactic may indeed add significant soloability to mages, at least in the low 60's.<br>
