<br>
<br>
I've played a druid (to level 61), wizard(to level 49), shaman(to level 53) and bard(to level 61).  Currently working a mage at level 40.<br>
<br>
<br>
So far, the shaman was the only soloer who could keep up with the mage.  <br>
<br>
Druid uses mana, so soloing pulls are limited to how fast you can regen.  You also hit a wall in the mid-50s in that the druids dots don't contiue to scale, so mobs take longer and longer to die.<br>
<br>
Wizard is king of the quadders, but very mana intensive with lots of downtime and requires lots of space to solo.<br>
<br>
Bard is an amazing creature, who can solo for hours on end and never sit down.  Too bad kills take 4-8 minutes at level 60.  Damage output is too low.<br>
<br>
The shaman can really tear through mobs, and is the most versatile soloing class I have played.  The combination of slow and mana regen makes him very efficient and fun to play.  Pet ain't half bad either.<br>
<br>
<br>
I would rate the magician as second behind the shaman, but ahead of the bard, wizard and druid in terms of soloability.<br>
<br>
The only 'solo' class I haven't tried is the necromancer.  <br>
<br>
As for enchanters soloing better than mages, maybe after they get DC.  Before that your statement is a joke. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cubicool>Cubicool</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 5:12:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Gallerus</span><hr size=1> Hmm.<br>
<br>
I wish I liked the Mage class. I've played one for so long and now I'm abandoning it.<br>
<br>
You can say what you want, there will ALWAYS be die hard fans, but the fact is that, when compared to other classes (which is, of couse, the ONLY WAY to judge the value of one class as it compares to another - comparing it to your environment is not only unfair but proportionlly irrelevant, you have to think &quot;What skills does a Mage ALWAYS have at his disposal?&quot; unless you just have fuzzy, blind love) the Mage is a total gimp. <br>
<br>
It sucks though, because I really grew to like my Mage. <br>
<br>
Some ideas that would make the Mage 1000000 times better:<br>
<br>
- Add an explode effect to Burnout. When the pet dies, it does an AOE stun, giving you an extra line of defense.<br>
<br>
- IMPROVE PET HP, AC, and ATK! <br>
<br>
- Improve Damage Shields, Mages should OWN this, hands down.<br>
<br>
- If we get CotH, fine. Make it work everywhere. <br>
<br>
- Allow us to buff our pets with one of two types of procs: One that would do extra damage and another that would siphon a small amount of mana from the MOB and give it to the master. Why not? Mage ARE their pets.<br>
<br>
Maybe I'm insane. But it's not asking too much. Of all the pure INT casters, and all the pure WIS priests, Mages are the LEAST desirable and almost the worst soloer (Cleric, being worse - maybe.)<br>
